Description:
CORNER 10 ACRE ALLOTMENT NEAR COAST!!!!
SHORT NOTICE AUCTION - SATURDAY 15TH JUNE @ 2PM.
OFFERS INVITED AND MAY BE ACCEPTED BEFORE AUCTION.
Looking for that change of lifestyle?????
This 10 acre property sits just outside the bayside area of Corinella yet is still within minutes to coast. The older style brick residence offers 4 bedrooms 3 of which have b/i/r's, master with en suite, formal lounge, cosy kitchen/meals area,
Family room with sliding door access to outside area, family bathroom with full bath and separate shower and the laundry has direct access to large mud room which is great for those muddy boots and raincoats coming in from the land.
Additional features include: 18 solar panels on home, solar panels on large shed, cattle ramp, 5 paddocks one with Lucerne, working cool room, large hayshed, 3 bay shed, dam, post and wire fencing, truck parking area.
This property has loads of potential - ideal for horse lovers or for the hobby farm enthusiast . Located within minutes 24 hour boat ramp, general shop, community centre, tennis courts, lawn bowls and hall. School bus nearby, local primary school and long day care centre within minutes and a small group of shops including permanent doctor , chemist, bank, newsagency , ambulance depot and cafes within 7 minutes. Phillip Island and major centre all within 25 minutes.
This is a rare opportunity to purchase 10 acres of good grazing land so close to the water.
OPEN HOMES: Saturday 25th May, 1st & 8th June - 1.30 to 2pm.

Description:
HUGE BLOCK 2600sqm approx - A WONDERFUL FAMILY HOME IN AN IDEAL LOCATION
Nestled in a very quiet area, and set on just over 1/2 acre, this classic country family home offers loads of yard that backs on to rural farmland with wonderful views.
Possible subdivide (STCA)
With only a moments drive to Bass Valley Primary School and the new Early Childhood Campus, walking distance to public transport and the beach at the end of the street.
Close to all the shops and services in Grantville. This property will suite those wanting space to create a rural beach side paradise.
Comprising
3 good sized bedrooms all with BIRs, great size kitchen, a light filled dining area, Lounge open plan living with cathedral ceilings, bathroom, good size laundry , wood fire, and reverse cycle split system.
Plus plenty of space for boats and caravan with loads of shedding .
Call Daniel & Tamara today to arrange your inspection
Please Note: Photo ID is required for all inspections

Description:
Prestigious South Gippsland Grazing Property
Prestigious South Gippsland (San Remo Peninsula) Grazing Property
Alex Scott and Staff Warragul are proud to present the opportunity to purchase this very impressive grazing property known as Bass Park.
Key features of the property -
• A total of 162 acres* consisting of 2 certificates of title
Title 1, 136 acres* with the circa 1905, 9 room homestead
Title 2, 26 acres* with the 4 bedroom brick home
• 162 acres of fertile river flats offering quality Rye and Clover Pastures, continuous fertiliser history
• Bass River frontage of approximately 1500 metres with a water entitlement, electric pressure pump supplying water to a header tank or mains water reticulated throughout the property.
• High quality capital improvements including all fencing and gates, very functional and centrally located stock facilities with under cover crush, central laneway system servicing the farm and yards, good shedding, stables and arena.
Main Residence
• Centrepiece of the property is the circa 1905 homestead, resplendent with Victorian character and period features which offers a spacious flexible floor plan including 4 large bedrooms, home office or 5th bedroom, 2 ensuites, family bathroom, provincial style kitchen, open plan living area, formal dining room, games room or rumpus room, northerly aspect, comfortably set amongst an old world garden of mature trees and well maintained gardens.
Second Residence
• Very comfortable 4 bedroom brick home, main bedroom with ensuite and BIR, central bathroom, open plan living/dining area, 9x6m2 shed
This glamorous property with outstanding infrastructure poses itself to various markets including but not limited to that unique lifestyle, productive beef operation or for a commercial use such as public functions, weddings and gatherings etc.
The property is privately located at the end of a no through road and within minutes of the Bass Village and Highway, Melbourne's eastern fringe is a 45 minutes* drive and 12 minutes* to Phillip Island.
Price:$2,300,000. Vendor finance available.
For more information or your private inspection please call John Patterson on 0413 565 408
*Approximately

Description:
Pristine, private and perfectly positioned
Idyllically positioned in Tenby Point and just moments walk to the water at the end of the street, this warm-hearted home offers a compelling blend of comfort, space and perfect privacy.
The open plan living and dinning area spills effortlessly in to a modern kitchen area. The home offers 2 bedrooms with BIR and carpet throughout, share bathroom. There is an entertaining deck out the back to sit and enjoy the morning sunrise and sunsets. The property size is approx. 1332m, and offers 2 driveway entrances. There is also a man cave shed or can be used has a great winter entertaining room with toilet and shower and wood fire and sunroom. The beautifully maintained property also includes reverse cycle heating and cooling and plenty of off-street parking, 2 water tanks, single roller door shed.
This beautiful residence offers an enchanting charm like none other. Sitting on approx. 1332m this block will indulge the lucky new owners with sanctuary- like living and an escape from the bustle of life, so many crave.

Description:
Convenience & Comfort
Phone Enquiry ID: 72124
$350,000 is a short term offer only.
A must see, this immaculately kept, low maintenance brick veneer open plan home offers a lifestyle of convenience and comfort. Nothing to do but move in, it is ideal for a family or retirees.
The good size kitchen includes all new white cupboards, benchtops and splashbacks. Equipped with a pantry, saucepan draws and a Westinghouse gas hotplate & oven with range hood.
Three large bedrooms, all with built-in robes with sliding mirror doors. There is also an ensuite to master and semi ensuite to the third bedroom. All bedrooms and lounge room are polished hardwood floors with tiled floors from the front door through to the kitchen, dining area, laundry, back door, main bathroom, ensuite & toilet. Walls of the main toilet, bathroom & bedroom ensuite are tiled to ceiling.
The Large bathroom has a free-standing bath & W/C and a separate laundry with built-in cupboard space allows for extra storage. All windows have been replaced with New Aluminium lockable windows with flyscreens.
The rear yard has a large shed on concrete, a small woodshed, a chicken pen and vegetable gardens with concrete paths and boundaries to all areas and fencing.
Other features include:
Fujitsu Reverse Cycle Air Con ASTG24MCA for up to 24 squares home.
Ultime 18 Supreme freestanding wood heater (heats up to 18 squares(. Half is tiled in same tiles as floors.
Matching light fittings throughout home.
New ceiling fans with remotes to lounge and bedrooms.
Matching drapes and curtains throughout home.
Bistro blinds on rear large deck area.
TV Ariel outlets to lounge (2) Bed 1 and Bed 3.
Insulation in all exterior walls and ceilings.
Solar.
Single Carport.
Parking for 3 cars in the driveway.
What more could you want? Dont miss this excellent opportunity to secure peaceful, quality living with nothing more to do!

Description:
Family home set to impress
Quality built and well maintained, this 4 bedroom home on 1400sqm presents like new and has a floor plan that will appeal to growing families. A spacious kitchen with a walk in pantry has all the storage you could want, adjoins the open-plan meals/family room, with easy access to the outdoor entertaining area. The master bedroom has a walk in robe and ensuite. The other bedrooms have built in robes with sliding doors. Further features include ducted heating and evaporative cooling, with ceiling fans throughout. There is also the added bonus of easy side access, colour bond shed and a big backyard. Built to a standard, not a price, this home is sure to bring years of happiness to the new owner. Inspections are by appointment.

OUR VENDOR SAYS SELL!

There are 3 good sized bedrooms throughout the home, one featuring a full wall of robes. Its an easy walk to the general store
and jetty while the school bus stop is right out the front. With heaps of space for the kids to run and play, a decked area to enjoy the warm nights and enough yard space to play with this property presents a fantastic lifestyle opportunity.

Description:
Four bedrooms & 3 living areas on huge 776sqm block (approx.)
Nestled in peaceful surroundings sits this outstanding family home that exudes warmth, style and has plenty of space sprawling over a generous 27 squares approx. All of the family will love the modern conveniences, excellent location and generous block size that this charming home has to offer.
- Formal lounge and dining at the front of the home in addition to an open plan, recently renovated kitchen/dining/family zone featuring a warm & cosy wood fire heater, ceiling fans & easy access to the covered pergola
- Open study/sitting room to the rear of the home
- Master bedroom with walk-in robe & ensuite with the remaining bedrooms all sizeable enough to home queen sized beds & completed with oversized double robes finished with Stegbar frameless mirrored sliding doors plus their own ceiling fans
- Central bathroom showcasing a luxurious spa bath plus open powder room
- Remote controlled double garage with rear roller door access to the rear yard perfect for a boat, caravan or trailer
- Further features: internal storage room, 2x garden sheds, raised vegetable gardens, 5kw solar panel system & ducted vacuum
Further complimenting the home is the ideal location, being within walking distance to the heart of the village & all the amenities and facilities on offer including shops, brewery, Lang Lang Primary School, public transport & with easy access to Westernport Highway and other major road arterials. Don't wait call Matt or Brent NOW to secure your inspection!

Description:
¼ ACRE BLOCK WITH WATER VIEWS
Situated on the corner of Anderson Parade and Barker Street is this double storey Hardiplank home. This property offers endless possibilities, is situated in an elevated location and is only a short walk to the Corinella and District Community Centre and Corinella General Store.
Entering up the external staircase you are greeted by a wonderful water view, stepping inside you enter into an open plan kitchen/lounge/dining area. The upstairs zones are complete with a family bathroom and 2x bedrooms. It has predominantly been used as a holiday home with minimal use of late.
The large yard includes many mature fruit trees along with other plants and a double car garage with extra undercover storage to one side. The yard could easily be transformed into your next landscaped masterpiece or kept as low maintenance for pets or children.
Note, the neighbouring 1/4 Acre block no. 23 Anderson Parade is also for sale.
Please contact the friendly team at Alex Scott and Staff - Bass Valley to book your inspection.
